cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.IR, cs.CL 

This paper deals with the analysis of tweets related to Ebola and the classification of those tweets into credible and speculative categories. This falls under the domain of social media analysis (cs.SOC) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also uses natural language processing techniques to extract features from the tweets, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses the spread of misinformation on social media, which is a topic of interest in the field of cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). Finally, the paper proposes a method for monitoring and separating speculative tweets from credible ones, which could be useful in the context of social media monitoring (cs.SI).
